                            <comment id="14456632" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 24 Dec 2014 19:33:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the entire code we use animal-sniffer-maven-plugin with signature java15 in src/main/java code.&lt;br/&gt;
This means the surefire project is built correctly with code base 1.5, whatever Maven dist 2.2.1/3.x is used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding IT(jetty-war-test-failing) Unsupported major.minor version 51.0 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;J2SE 7 = 51 (0x33 hex)&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, this failure appears due to ${java.home} refers to JDK5. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Due to these problems, we should use JUnit assumptions in beginning of IT which only ignores the tests for JDK &amp;lt; 7:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;org.hamcrest:hamcrest-library:1.3:test&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
import static org.hamcrest.Matchers.*;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;assumeThat( jvmMajor, is( 1 ) )&lt;br/&gt;
assumeThat( jvmMinor, is( greaterThanOrEqualTo( 7 ) ) )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because of these tests require JDK 7 and because of no-test-avoidance, we should state in README.txt that JDK 7 is preferable in order to get bigger test coverage.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
